cs.SE, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.PL. 

The paper focuses on identifying algorithm names in code comments, which is a software engineering task. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. However, the paper also uses natural language processing techniques to extract important N-gram words and considers part of speech patterns, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (finding valuable data sources) and programming languages (C, C++, Java, JavaScript, Python, PHP, and Ruby), which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
